    <briefdescription>
<para>Concrete NFA implementations of algorithms, such as complement, inclusion, or universality checking. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>This is a separation of the implementation from the interface defined in <computeroutput><ref refid="namespacemata_1_1nfa" kindref="compound">mata::nfa</ref></computeroutput>. <simplesect kind="note"><para>In <computeroutput><ref refid="namespacemata_1_1nfa" kindref="compound">mata::nfa</ref></computeroutput> interface, there are particular dispatch functions calling these function according to parameters provided by a user. E.g., we can call the following function: <lsquo/>is_universal(aut, alph, {{&apos;algorithm<rsquo/>, &apos;antichains&apos;}})` to check for universality based on antichain-based algorithm. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
